            <pb n="1"/>
            <p>The <addressee>Revd Isaac Leeser</addressee>,</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">Dr Sir,</p>
            <p rend="indent(2)">I have to acknowledge<lb/> yours of <date>29th</date> ultimo and to
                thank<lb/> you for acceding to my request<lb/> respecting my little work,<lb/> which
                will <add>?</add> be published<lb/> here on <date>1st July</date>, and I will<lb/>
                endeavor to sent you 1 doz<lb/> copies as near that<add>?</add> time as<lb/>
                possible. I concluded from<lb/> your note <add>?</add> it that<lb/> you are
                agreeable to the<lb/> terms I proposed, 25 pc commission.<lb/> I think my book must
                be<lb/> rebound cheap even in the<lb/> American sense of the word,<lb/> as each part
                will comprise</p>
            <pb n="2"/>
            <p>about 180 pages of matter, with the<lb/> best paper and type for 2/<add>?</add><lb/>
                a part. It<add>?</add> will I hope be concluded in <date>October</date><lb/> I have
                a first rate list of<lb/> subscribers all the heads of<lb/> the nation <persName>Dr
                    Adler</persName>
                <persName>Sir Moses<lb/> Montefiore</persName><add>?</add> the
                    <persName>Rothschild's</persName><lb/>
                <add>?</add> and <persName>Dr Berusch</persName><lb/> has introduced it very
                favorably<lb/> to public notice in the Hebrew<lb/> Observer. I shall be obliged<lb/>
                by your putting in the follow<lb/>ing <sic>advertizement</sic> in the<lb/> Occident
                for <date>July</date>, and I should<lb/> wish it continued till
                <date>October</date><lb/> when you will please alter<lb/> it to announce the
                second<lb/> part; though I will write<lb/> previously in case any thing<lb/> should
                prevent its publication<lb/> at that time.</p>
            <pb n="3"/>
            <p>“To be published in two parts<lb/> price 2/. each part.</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">Now ready Post<add>?</add>
                <add>?</add><lb/>
                <date>Sabbath</date> Evenings at Home<lb/> or<lb/>
                <add>?</add> Conversations on the<lb/> Jewish Religion its Spirit<lb/> and
                Observances by</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)"><persName>Mi<add>?</add> Mendes Belesario</persName><lb/> Published
                in <placeName>London</placeName> by <persName>Mes Joel</persName><lb/>
                <placeName>42 South Cripplegate</placeName>. To be had<lb/> in <placeName>New
                    York</placeName> of <persName>Mr Daniel Wolff</persName><lb/>
                <placeName>32 South St.</placeName>
                <placeName>Philadelphia</placeName>
                <persName>Revd<lb/> Isaac Leeser</persName> &amp;</p>
            <p>You will please put this in<lb/> proper order for me.<lb/> and now having
                concluded<lb/> my business arrangements,<lb/> permit me Dr Sir to express my<lb/>
                sincere regret for the severe<add>?</add><lb/> loss you have sustained by<lb/> the
                fire, for which I trust<lb/> you may meet with compen<lb/>sation by an increased
                sale<lb/> of your books, in which business <add>?</add></p>
            <pb n="4"/>
            <p>it will not be in my power to<lb/> assist you, at least as regards the<lb/> Prayer
                Books; for of course our<lb/>
                <add>?</add> consisted<add>?</add>
                <persName>Mr De Sola's</persName><lb/> are in general circulation among<lb/> our
                congregation. I understand<lb/> you contemplate reprinting his<lb/> in
                    <placeName>America</placeName>, and that your<lb/> dependence lies there, for
                I<lb/> think it right to <add>?</add> that<lb/> you are not likely to meet<lb/> with
                much support here. You<lb/> have <add>?</add> been misinformed<lb/> as to
                    <persName>Mr Genese's</persName> influence<lb/> he could do nothing
                whatever<lb/> I regret much to find that<lb/> you have still so many powerful<lb/>
                things to contend with, but<lb/> think you are mistaken in<lb/> your impression of
                    <persName>Mr Morais</persName><lb/> unless he be greatly altered, for<lb/> I
                knew him intimately, very<lb/> deep knowledge of Hebrew is<lb/> derived from him,
                and I</p>
            <pb n="5"/>
            <p>should have thought he would<lb/> rather have songlets<add>?</add> to heal than<lb/>
                    forment<add>?</add> discord However as one<lb/> who has so warmly
                <add>?</add><lb/> the blessings of brotherly union<lb/> I trust you will still find
                    young<add>?</add><lb/> the respected <add>?</add> of your old<lb/> friendly
                circle and that you<lb/> will remember by conceding<lb/> a little you will be
                conferring<lb/> a real blessing on your opponents<lb/> as well as the Israelites
                generally<lb/> by <add>?</add> them again to<lb/> profit by your servant
                teaching<lb/> and piety Believe me that<lb/> I have and shall ever promote<lb/> the
                circulation of your books<lb/> to the utmost of my power<lb/> with the exception of
                the Prayer<lb/> Books which I could not do<lb/> conscientiously without acting</p>
            <pb n="6"/>
            <p>unhandsomely by <persName>Mr De Sola</persName> or<lb/> you will acknowledge
                that<lb/> often the toil and expense<lb/> they have cost him it would<lb/> be unfair
                for one of his<lb/> own flock to help another<lb/> to keep the benefit. My
                cousins<lb/> the <persName>Misses Belisario</persName> have kindly<lb/> taken a
                large supply of your<lb/> Catechisms I believe 30—6 reading<lb/> books—a number of
                    <persName>Peixotto</persName>—<lb/>1 large Bible and 3 copies of<lb/> sermons
                for their Establishment</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">I must now conclude</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">remaining dear sir</p>
            <p rend="indent(2)">very truly yours</p>
            <p rend="indent(2)">
                <persName role="author">M<add>?</add> M Belisario</persName>
            </p>
            <p>
                <date>23d May/56</date>
            </p>
            <p>
                <placeName>50 Liverpool St.</placeName>
            </p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">
                <placeName>King's City</placeName>
            </p>
